  "prompt": "What universities does Concert Pharmaceuticals recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Concert Pharmaceuticals, a biotechnology company focused on developing innovative medicines, typically recruits new graduates with strong academic backgrounds in fields relevant to their work. While specific university preferences may not be publicly disclosed, companies like Concert Pharmaceuticals often recruit from prestigious institutions known for their strong programs in the life sciences, chemistry, and related disciplines. These may include:\n\n### Universities:\n- **Ivy League schools** (e.g., Harvard, MIT, Yale, Princeton)\n- **Top-ranked public universities** (e.g., University of California system, University of Michigan, University of Wisconsin-Madison)\n- **Leading research institutions** (e.g., Stanford, Johns Hopkins, University of Chicago)\n- **Specialized schools** (e.g., Caltech, Carnegie Mellon, Duke)\n\n### Majors/Training:\nConcert Pharmaceuticals is likely to seek candidates with expertise in the following areas:\n- **Life Sciences**: Biology, Biochemistry, Molecular Biology, Cell Biology\n- **Chemistry**: Organic Chemistry, Medicinal Chemistry, Chemical Biology\n- **Pharmaceutical Sciences**: Drug Discovery, Pharmacology\n- **Engineering**: Chemical Engineering, Biomedical Engineering\n- **Computational Sciences**: Bioinformatics, Data Science\n- **Business/Regulatory**: For roles in business development, regulatory affairs, or clinical operations\n\n### Key Skills and Experience:\n- Research experience (e.g., lab work, internships, or co-ops)\n- Strong analytical and problem-solving skills\n- Familiarity with drug discovery and development processes\n- Knowledge of industry regulations and compliance (for certain roles)\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, check Concert Pharmaceuticals' **careers page** or their presence at **university career fairs** and recruiting events. Networking with current employees or alumni from your institution can also provide insights into their hiring practices.",
